                            <comment id="477108" author="rread" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2025 19:15:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrating with the existing build/test infrastructure is the goal, though it may take some time to get there. &#160;Currently main crate name is rustreapi, so I&apos;d like to stick with that to make it clear this is the user space api, not the filesystem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="477103" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2025 19:02:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we could add a Rust toolchain to Jenkins nodes, it be nice to validate that the bindings builld. Otherwise, it&apos;d be hard to ensure they stay up-to-date. I don&apos;t know if you&apos;re planning to publish to crates.io, but lustre seems available - &lt;a href=&quot;https://crates.io/crates/lustre&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://crates.io/crates/lustre&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
